  "prompt": "How long do you bake one chicken breast?",
  "response": "The baking time for one chicken breast depends on its size and the oven temperature. Here\u2019s a general guideline:\n\n1. **Preheat the oven** to 375\u00b0F (190\u00b0C).\n2. **Prepare the chicken breast**: Pat it dry, season it, and optionally coat it with oil or butter.\n3. **Bake** for **20\u201330 minutes** for an average-sized (6\u20138 oz or 170\u2013230 g) chicken breast.\n4. **Check for doneness**: The internal temperature should reach 165\u00b0F (74\u00b0C) when measured with a meat thermometer inserted into the thickest part.\n\nFor larger or thicker breasts, you may need to add a few extra minutes. If the chicken is smaller or thinner, reduce the baking time slightly to avoid overcooking. If you\u2019re baking multiple breasts, ensure they\u2019re spaced evenly on the baking sheet to cook evenly.",
